<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900614-0045</DOCNO><DOCID>900614-0045.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- H.H. Robertson Co.:   Pittsburgh Firm Progresses   Toward Funding Ceco Deal</HL><DATE>06/14/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8</SO><CO>   T.FCY RHH X.CKO</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)BUILDING MATERIALS (BLD)</IN><LP>   H.H. Robertson Co. said it is making progress in arrangingfinancing for the acquisition of Ceco Industries Inc.,Oakbrook Terrace, Ill.   Robertson, a building products and contracting concern inPittsburgh, said it received a written commitment from WellsFargo Bank for $150 million of financing. In addition,Frontera S.A., a Swiss investment company, definitivelyagreed to buy $40 million of Robertson stock after themerger.</LP><TEXT>   Robertson had agreed earlier to pay $15 million cash plus3.4 million to 4.1 million shares of Robertson common stockfor the closely held Ceco, and to assume $85 million of Cecodebt. Following the transaction, Frontera and the currentowners of Ceco each would own about 25% of Robertson'soutstanding shares.   Ceco manufactures doors, metal buildings and roof systems,and is a provider of concrete forming services.</TEXT></DOC>